Preheat the oven to 160°C. Trim the @spring onion{1}(finely sliced). Zest and quarter the @lime{1}.

Chop the base off the @pak choi{1} and discard. Slice lengthways into quarters.

Peel and grate the @ginger{1}. Separate the bok choy leaves and pop onto a #baking tray{} with a drizzle of oil, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on the top shelf of the oven for ~{10-12%minutes}, until tender and slightly charred. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, chop the @firm tofu{280%g} into 2cm cubes. Lay them on some #kitchen paper{} to soak up some of the moisture.

Pop the @cornflour{20%g} onto a #large plate{}. Season heavily with pepper.

Pop the tofu onto the plate. Toss to evenly coat the tofu in the cornflour.

Heat a drizzle of oil in #large frying pan{} over high heat.

Pop the tofu into the pan (leaving any excess cornflour behind!). Fry until golden all over, ~{6-8%minutes}, turning occasionally.

Tip the tofu into a #bowl{} and set aside. Keep the pan.

Cook the @steamed basmati rice{1} according to the pack instructions.

Meanwhile, pop the ginger and half the spring onion into the now empty #frying pan{} over medium heat (add a drizzle of oil if needed).

Cook for ~{1%minute}, stirring continuously.

Add the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @ketjap manis{25%ml}, @mirin{15%ml}, @sugar{1/4%tsp} and @sesame oil{24%ml} to the pan.

Return the tofu to the pan and stir through the teriyaki sauce (that you just made) to heat through, allowing it to bubble and thicken slightly.

Divide the cooked rice between your #bowls{} and stir through the lime zest and remaining spring onion.

Stir the @sesame seeds{15} and the juice from half your lime wedges into the tofu and sauce.

Serve the rice in bowls with the teriyaki tofu on top. Pop the bok choy and leftover lime wedges on the side. Enjoy!